videos.description: Duke's Frank Jackson turns a steal into a two-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Jackson makes Clemson pay with steal and dunk

videos.description: Duke's Jayson Tatum finishes at the hoop with a one-handed slam.
videos.headline: Tatum punishes rim with one-handed dunk

videos.description: Sidy Djitte goes up for a two-handed slam, but is fouled in the process.
videos.headline: Clemson draws foul on huge missed dunk

videos.description: Duke's Grayson Allen is given a technical foul after slamming the ball in front of an official.
videos.headline: Allen's frustration leads to technical foul

videos.description: Duke's Jayson Tatum uses a spin move and gets through traffic for the bucket.
videos.headline: Tatum spins and splits defenders on beautiful layup

videos.description: Clemson head coach Brad Brownell talks about Jaron Blossomgame's first half play and defensive adjustment's for the second half.
videos.headline: Brad Brownell on Blossomgame's first half performance

videos.description: Duke's Frank Jackson almost loses control of the ball but manages to score on a fastbreak layup assisted by Luke Kennard.
videos.headline: Jackson fumbles pass on way to layup

videos.description: Duke's Jayson Tatum gets fouled as he drives the baseline for a great reverse layup.
videos.headline: Tatum drives the baseline for reverse layup

videos.description: Clemson looks to save the ball off a Duke miss, but Jayson Tatum has other ideas as he steals the ball back and goes in for a one-handed dunk.
videos.headline: Tatum impresses with heads-up dunk

videos.description: Duke's Jayson Tatum discusses his offensive play vs. Clemson and Duke's defensive adjustments in the 2nd half.
videos.headline: Tatum on his offensive performance against Clemson
